So theres not much changed in this map, but i made this version from one reason.. I think its the best map i've made, but way underplayed... 

So i figured out that, if you play the lvls individually, like normal bhop maps, where you have to beat the first lvl to get to the second..

This map has that now, you do it one by one... Which means you can run it with a counter aswell.. 

I hope this will give you guys more use of my map :) 

Enjoy!

I hope you will like this map and find it enjoyable. I tried to make some diffrent looks with more details than i usually do in my maps. Overall i spent a good amount of time creating this map. 

About the bonus lvl. Its more like a lvl just to let you get a weapon with trial. Its not hard at all, and you might think its too easy. Bonus lvl will be playable when all the other lvls are done.

Have Fun.

A 2:20-2:30 long (if you're going fast) strafe map. I got bored and wanted to make a bit of a longer map so I spent a few days working on this, it's pretty straight forward and has a big block style, the map is easy to beat in general but hard to do fast. I intended for it to be a one shot map, but decided to add a few checkpoints here and there because I knew some people would complain.  

The bonus was originally made by Dream for a surf project of mine, it was then modified by ArcticPanda and finally changed slightly by me.  

Map should be doable on all styles, just keep in mind the map is intended to be ran with a lot of speed so if you keep failing you might find yourself pre-speeding a lot.

Hi,

This map was made as a joke for my friends on Verge bhop and was intended as a weekend project. I ended up working on this map for awhile off and on. There was no planning, everything was just off the top of my head, and therefore it is pretty shitty. There's some silly features like the bonus overlay and the music room.

I had to redo a lot of parts due to various issues, which caused me to be a bit lazy when redoing them. So if there are any problems please tell me. There is an render overflow if you go into void that I cant fix without making the light source detail into props or func_detail which would ruin the lighting.

Tested on all settings including 400 velocity limit

Textures were ripped from google images, grayed out in Photoshop then added color overlays.
Constructive criticism would be appreciated as this is my first finished map. Parts you like, parts you didn't like.

Hello everyone, Im pleased to announce the release of bhop_megasphere! There's been alot of blood sweat and tears to get this into the state it is today, also figuring out how the hell to make a really good bhop map work in the Source engine, but Im pretty proud of how it looks and plays now. It should run well on most systems with a RTX 2080 TI / XFX Nvidia Geforce 8600GT  or above, not sure about below that as I havent been able to test on lower end systems. ========= Thanks to everyone who offered feedback and advice on this map, its been a big challenge and a hard journey and I hope you have fun!

_sText:
bhop_lost_world_v2

General Map Info

After approximately 6 months of "casual" development I managed to bring this map to it's final stage. The map features adventuristic atmosphere throughout easy to medium difficulty bhops. While map is big it should keep you busy for quite some time, as it features better achievement concept. It should be possible for large variety of players to finish the map.

Map Features

  • Very big world
  • Variety of different bunny hop concepts
  • Decent difficulty scale
  • Puzzles
  • Most content is custom
  • Achievement system
  • Unique mini-game
  • Special rewards
  • Custom soundscapes
Extra Notes
My hopes are that you will enjoy playing this map as much as I enjoyed making it. The v2 update took total of 2 weeks full time development. Enjoy
